<p>Email consistently delivers a <b>30&#8211;40x ROI</b>.</p>

<p>That&#8217;s true in B2C.</p>

<p>It&#8217;s true in B2B too &#8212; just a little less directly.</p>

<p>And the reason isn&#8217;t complicated.</p>

<p>There are three forces working in email&#8217;s favor.</p>

<p>First: <b>it&#8217;s cheap</b>.</p>

<p>Once you have an email list, sending to it costs almost nothing.</p>

<p>There&#8217;s no per-send fee like SMS.<br>
No paying people by the hour like cold calling.<br>
No &#8220;one-to-one&#8221; transportation cost.</p>

<p>Email is <b>one-to-many</b>, at near-zero marginal cost.</p>

<p>You also don&#8217;t need to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Produce a new video every week</li>
  <li>Be on camera</li>
  <li>Win an algorithm</li>
</ul>

<p>A single piece of written content can reach thousands of people at once.</p>

<p>And with modern tooling (including AI), producing that content is cheaper than it&#8217;s ever been.</p>

<p>No rising CPMs.<br>No bidding wars.<br>No paying again for the same attention.</p>

<p>Every send is leverage on spend you already made.</p>

<p>Second: <b>intent is higher in the inbox</b>.</p>

<p>People don&#8217;t open email to kill time.</p>

<p>They&#8217;re:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Checking receipts</li>
  <li>Booking travel</li>
  <li>Reviewing orders</li>
  <li>Making decisions</li>
</ul>

<p>That kind of attention matters.</p>

<p>An impression in a social feed is passive.</p>

<p>An impression in the inbox is active.</p>

<p>That&#8217;s why email converts better.</p>

<p>It reaches people when they&#8217;re already in a buying mindset &#8212; not when they&#8217;re scrolling to be entertained.</p>

<p>Third: <b>email is an owned audience</b>.</p>

<p>No algorithm decides who sees your message.<br>
No platform can throttle your reach overnight.<br>
No luck required.</p>

<p>You invest in your list over time.<br>
You build a sender reputation.<br>
You consistently hit the inbox.</p>

<p>It&#8217;s not a casino.</p>

<p>It&#8217;s an asset.</p>

<p>And here&#8217;s the part most businesses miss:</p>

<p>Email converts <b>bottom-line revenue</b>.</p>

<p>You already paid for these leads.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Ads</li>
  <li>Events</li>
  <li>Sales conversations</li>
</ul>

<p>New leads are great &#8212; but your list is where the easiest wins live.</p>

<p>When you nurture it properly, every conversion is profit you didn&#8217;t have to re-buy.</p>

<p>That&#8217;s why the ROI is so high.</p>

<p>Low cost.<br>High intent.<br>Owned distribution.</p>

<p>That&#8217;s the email advantage.</p>

